(== Microcontrollers & Wireless ==) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Component Name: Espressif ESP8266EX \(ESP8266-based module; exact module variant not specified in firmware\) - Wi?Fi MCU/SoC) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Operating Voltage: 2.5?3.6 V \(nominal 3.3 V\). Firmware drives GPIO directly; assumes 3.3 V logic domain.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Current Consumption: Firmware does not implement sleep; expect Wi?Fi active/idle currents per datasheet. Typical: ~70?80 mA average during active Wi?Fi, with TX peaks commonly >170 mA. Deep-sleep current \(datasheet\) is typically in the tens of µA, but deep-sleep is not used by this firmware.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Communication Protocol: UART0 \(Serial debug\) @ 115200 baud; IEEE 802.11 b/g/n 2.4 GHz Wi?Fi; HTTP\(S\) client to backend \(ESP8266HTTPClient\) with TLS enabled but certificate validation disabled via setInsecure\(\); captive portal HTTP server on port 80 and DNS server on port 53; NTP over UDP \(pool.ntp.org\) update interval 3600000 ms.) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Datasheet Link: https://documentation.espressif.com/0a-esp8266ex_datasheet_en.html) Tj
0 -12 Td
