(== Actuators ==) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Component Name: Tower Pro MG996R \(as referenced by firmware comment\) - high-torque servo motor \(firmware uses continuous/feeding pulses via Servo.h\)) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Operating Voltage: 4.8?6.6 V \(per manufacturer product spec\). Control signal is PWM from ESP8266 GPIO \(3.3 V logic\).) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Current Consumption: Firmware does not calculate motor current. Manufacturer specs list idle ~10 mA, no-load ~170 mA, stall ~1400 mA \(ensure power supply margin\).) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Communication Protocol: Servo PWM control \(Servo.h\). Typical 50 Hz pulse train; firmware sets pulse widths in microseconds \(neutral 1500 µs; feed pulses around 1550?1680 µs; anti-jam reverse pulses ~1400 µs\).) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Datasheet Link: https://towerpro.com.tw/product/mg996r/) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Firmware Evidence:) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  - Firmware.ino:L7-L9 \(MG996R servo referenced in header comment\)) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  - Firmware.ino:L36-L81 \(SERVO_* pulse definitions\)) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  - Firmware.ino:L264-L267 \(Servo.attach + writeMicroseconds usage\)) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  - Firmware.ino:L279-L327 \(feeding control + ramping logic\)) Tj
0 -12 Td
(Discrepancy Flags:) Tj
0 -12 Td
(  - Firmware assumes continuous rotation behavior \(feeding\) while MG996R is commonly an angle servo; continuous behavior may depend on mechanical modification or a continuous-rotation variant. Verify the exact servo variant used on the hardware.) Tj
